input: Country: Spain. Purchaser Name: RECTORATE OF THE POLYTECHNIC UNIVERSITY OF VALENCIA. Summary: Supply of Laptops for the Polytechnic University of Valencia. Description: The Universitat Politècnica de València (UPV) has a laptop loan service aimed at guaranteeing that all students can access digital teaching resources and the necessary tools under equal conditions. for the development of their academic activity. This service constitutes a key element to minimize the digital divide and ensure that no student is excluded due to lack of adequate technological means. In recent years, a significant part of the laptop fleet currently available has reached the end of its technological useful life. Specifically, many computers cannot be updated to the Windows 11 operating system as they do not meet the minimum security and hardware requirements, among which stands out the absence of TPM 2.0 modules or other functionalities necessary to guarantee secure boot, system integrity and data protection. This limitation prevents equipment from being maintained in conditions that comply with the policies. cybersecurity institutions and current standards for protection against threats. As a consequence, said equipment is no longer suitable for academic use and cannot continue to be safely integrated into the IT infrastructure of the University. Furthermore, the physical deterioration associated with its age and the increasing difficulty in obtaining spare parts increase the risk of interruptions in the loan service, affecting.... Description: Manufacture and supply of conical stainless steel bodies by repulsing with welding without filler to obtain anti-implosion covers for 20-inch photomultipliers for the exp... Within the framework of its research activity, the LSC participates in the international project Hyper-Kamiokande (HK), a new generation experiment aimed at the study of neutrinos, proton decay and other fundamental phenomena of particle physics. HK constitutes the evolution of the Kamiokande and Super-Kamiokande detectors, whose results were recognized with the Nobel Prize in Physics in 2002 and 2015 respectively. The Hyper-Kamiokande detector will be built at a depth of approximately 620 meters underground in the town of Kamioka (Japan). It will consist of a large cylindrical tank about 70 meters in diameter and 70 meters high, filled with ultrapure water, on whose walls tens of thousands of photomultiplier tubes (PMTs) will be installed. These detectors record the Cherenkov light produced when charged particles, such as neutrinos, interact with water. Each PMT operates under high vacuum conditions, and due to the high hydrostatic pressure to which they are subjected, equivalent to a water column of 70 meters, there is a risk of implosion in the event of spontaneous failure of any PMT. This phenomenon, which occurs in milliseconds, can generate a shock wave capable of damaging adjacent PMTs and compromising the integrity of the experiment. To mitigate this risk, the experiment design incorporates an anti-implosion protective cover composed of two main elements: a material dome.... Published Date: 2025-12-19. Closing Date: 2026-01-27. Competition: ICB. Financier Name: Self Financed

input: Country: Spain. Purchaser Name: GENERAL SECRETARIAT OF THE CENTER FOR ENERGY, ENVIRONMENTAL AND TECHNOLOGICAL RESEARCH (CIEMAT). Summary: Supply of Liquid Helium and Liquid Nitrogen for the Tj-Ii Ecrh System. Description: The CIEMAT, and specifically the National Fusion Laboratory, for the development of its activity, has an experimental device called TJ-II in which the physics of plasma is studied. A system is used to heat said plasma, called Electronic Cyclotronic Resonance Warming (ECRH). This system consists of three high-power microwave emitters (gyrotrons) and all their associated systems. Each of these gyrotrons is immersed in a magnetic field static generated by superconducting coils that need to be brought to superconducting temperatures through the constant supply of cryogenic gases. Each coil is housed in a cryostat with two separate volumes, an inner one filled with helium liquid and another exterior filled with liquid nitrogen. Liquid helium supply for the TJ-II ECRH system The liquid He supply will be used to cool the TJ-II's superconducting coils. Supply of liquid nitrogen for the TJ-II ECRH system The liquid nitrogen supply will be used to cool the TJ-II superconducting coils. Doc Title: Supply of liquid helium and liquid nitrogen for the TJ-II ECRH system Contract Type: supplies. Published Date: 2025-12-17. Closing Date: 2026-01-23. Competition: ICB.
